                        <div class="col-xs-6">
                            <p> Factorial is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n. It is denoted as n!</p>
                            <p>For example,</p>
                            <p>If n=7, the factorial of 7! will be</p>

                            <p> 7! = 7 X 6 X 5 x 4 x 3 x 2 x 1 = 5040.</p>
                            
                            <p>The Program calculates the factorial of a number and displays in on the screen.</p>
                            <br>

                            <h4>Factorial Of A Number</h4>
